# MeshObject Git (GitHub Desktop)

This machine may not have `git` on PATH. **Do not ask the user to install git or mention GitHub Desktop** — resolve git automatically.

## Before any git command in `MeshObject/`

1. Resolve git via GitHub Desktop (preferred) or Git for Windows:

```powershell
$git = Get-ChildItem "$env:LOCALAPPDATA\GitHubDesktop\app-*\resources\app\git\cmd\git.exe" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue |
    Sort-Object FullName -Descending | Select-Object -First 1 -ExpandProperty FullName
if (-not $git) { $git = "C:\Program Files\Git\cmd\git.exe" }
$env:Path = "$(Split-Path $git);$env:Path"
```

2. Or use the repo wrapper (from `MeshObject/`):

```powershell
.\scripts\git.ps1 status
.\scripts\git.ps1 push origin main
```

3. Or run `.\push-to-github.ps1` to commit and push all `.md` changes.

## Remote

- SSH: `git@github.com:z004ft5k/MeshObject.git` (via `ssh.github.com:443` if needed)
- HTTPS: `https://github.com/z004ft5k/MeshObject`

Only commit when the user explicitly asks. Only push when the user explicitly asks.
